__activateTstore().details: External function to activate TSTORE usage. Does not need to be      called if TSTORE is supported from deployment, and only needs to be      called once. Reverts if TSTORE has already been activated or if the      opcode is not available. Note that this must be called directly from      an externally-owned account to avoid potential reentrancy issues.

cleanupErc20s(address[],address[],uint25.details: Should be included in the multicall if the router is expecting to receive tokens         Set amount to 0 to transfer the full balance

params.recipients: The addresses to refund the tokens to
params.tokens: The addresses of the ERC20 tokens

cleanupNative(uint256,address).details: Set amount to 0 to transfer the full balance. Set recipient to address(0) to transfer to msg.sender

params.amount: The amount of native tokens to transfer

multicall((address,bool,uint256,bytes)[].details: If a multicall is expecting to mint ERC721s or ERC1155s, the recipient must be explicitly set         All calls to ERC721s and ERC1155s in the multicall will have the same recipient set in recipient         Be sure to transfer ERC20s or ETH out of the router as part of the multicall

params.nftRecipient: The address to set as recipient of ERC721/ERC1155 mints
params.refundTo: The address to refund any leftover ETH to

cleanupNative(uint256,address).notice: Send leftover native tokens to the recipient address
